cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS

This paper proposes a technique for neural network learning that reduces computational cost and overfitting. It is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with improving the learning process of neural networks. It may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it proposes a method for updating the weights of neural networks. Additionally, it could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with improving the performance of AI models. The paper also mentions experiments on image classification, which suggests it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the technique involves sparsification of gradient vectors, which could be related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it involves manipulating data structures.
